sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch printenv' command
# Terminal function that displays environment variables in isolated context
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Executes commands to display all environment variables
#   Useful for debugging .env file loading and environment isolation
#   Shows exactly what variables are available in run_env() context
#
# Function behavior:
#   - Generates commands to display sorted environment variables
#   - Includes header/footer for readability
#   - Uses 'sh' interpreter to execute commands and show environment
#
# Debug workflow:
#   1. Check if .env files are loading correctly
#   2. Verify VPN_SWITCH_BASE propagation
#   3. Confirm VPN_SWITCH_ENV_DIR derivation
#   4. Validate VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_* variables
#
# Example usage:
#   vpn-switch printenv                    # Show current environment
#   VPN_SWITCH_BASE=/test vpn-switch printenv  # Test with custom base
#
# Advanced - show commands without executing (for debugging):
#   echo "cat" > .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_printenv
#   vpn-switch printenv                    # Show commands only
#
# See ARCHITECTURE.md for details on the interpreter system and run_env() isolation
